{"key":"processedPost-9472052","value":{"id":9472052,"first":9471940,"last":9472069,"when":1229880746,"utime":"12/21/08 07:32 PM","content":"As RK said, if you're growing cubes, consider a 1\" casing layer MAXimum.&nbsp; However, if you're using a bulk substrate, I see little to no benefit in even using a casing layer.&nbsp; Bulk substrates fruit as well or sometimes better without a casing layer at all, and you get your fruits a week sooner.&nbsp; In the old days, a casing layer helped to make up for sloppy humidity control.&nbsp; If you'll keep watch of your humidity and keep it in the upper 90's, just skip the darned casing.<br />RR","title":"Re: Casing layer proportionate to substrate?"}}